X, 78, 8.\n\nratha, chariot: rathe, II, 34, 7; rathai _h_ -iva, V, 60, 1; rathanam na ara\xc2\xb4\n_h_ , like the spokes of chariot-wheels, X, 78, 4.--rathe, Indra's chariot, I,\n6, 2.--ratha _h_ , the chariots of the Maruts, I, 38, 12; V, 55, 1 to 9; (V,\n87, 3:2; VI, 66, 2:1); rathan, V, 53, 5:1; rathebhi _h_ , I, 88, 1; V, 58, 6;\nrathai _h_ , VIII, 7, 17; (VIII, 20, 2:1); rathanam, V, 52, 9; 53, 10; VIII,\n94, 1; ratheshu, I, 39, 6; 64, 9; 85, 4; 5; 87, 2; 166, 9; II, 34, 8; V, 53,\n2; 4; 56, 6; 7; 57, 6; 60, 2; 4; 61, 12; VIII, 20, 12.--ratham, the chariot of\nthe Maruts, I, 167, 5; V, 56, 8; rathena, VIII, 20, 10; rathasya, I, 88, 2;\nrathe, V, 54, 11; 56, 6; VIII, 7, 28; 20, 8:1.--rathasya (Vata's), X, 168, I.\n--rathena (Vayu's), I, 134, 1; rathe, I, 134, 3.\n\nratha-tur, hastening the chariots: rathatu\xc2\xb4 _h_ -bhi _h_ , I, 88, 2; rathatu\xc2\xb4\n_h_ , X, 77, 8.\n\nratha-vat, consisting of chariots: ratha-vat ra\xc2\xb4dha _h_ , V, 57, 7.\n\nRatha-viti Darbhya: ([359](sbe3243.htm#page_359) seq.;\n[362](sbe3243.htm#page_362)); (V, 61, 5:2); ratha-vitau, V, 61, 18; ratha-viti\n_h_ , V, 61, 19.\n\nrathiyanti: rathiyanti-iva, whirling like chariot-wheels, I, 166, 5:3\n\nrathi\xc2\xb4, charioteer: rathi\xc2\xb4 _h_ -iva, V, 61, 17; rathya\xcc\x83 _h_ na, V, 87, 8;\nrathya _h_ , VII, 56, 21. rathya\xcc\x83 _h_ (didhishava _h_ ), lords of chariots, X,\n78, 5.--rathya\xcc\x83 _h_ syama, let us carry off, V, 54, 13:1.\n\nrathiyanti, see rathiyanti.\n\nrathe- _s_ ubh, brilliant on chariots: rathe- _s_ ubham, I, 37, I; V, 56, 9.\n\nrathya: rathya _h_ sapti _h_ , (I, 85, 1:1.)\n\nrad, to scratch, to bite: radati, I, 166, 6:4; rad, to cut, to give,\n([222](sbe3227.htm#page_222) seq.)\n\nrada, radana, tooth: (I, 166, 6:4.)\n\nradhra, wretched, a sluggard: radhram, II, 34, 15:1; VII, 56, 20:1; radhra and\nbh _r i_mi, (II, 34, 1:6.)\n\nrandhra, hollow: uksh _n_ a _h_ randhram, 'the hollow of the bull,' VIII, 7,\n26:1\n\nrap, to whisper: (II, 33, 3:1).--me arapat prati